A nice article in Escapist magazine about gaming in libraries. Hard to choose just a small section to quote but definitely give it a read. The issue can be downloaded in PDF as well.
&ldquo;That&rsquo;s one way to do it,&rdquo; Neiburger said, &ldquo;but what I&rsquo;m always telling people is it&rsquo;s extremely difficult to offer a videogame collection that doesn&rsquo;t look like crap next to what&rsquo;s offered at Blockbuster.&rdquo;
The tournament program in Ann Arbor is actually a gaming season that plays out over a few months, culminating in one final tournament. Prizes are given to the winners, and gamers who grow out of the teenage bracket have a chance to enter the Hall of Fame.
&ldquo;These kids feel totally differently about the institution than they ever did before,&rdquo; Neiburger said, &ldquo;because we&rsquo;re meeting them where they want to be rather than trying to shove classics down their throat.&quot;

